Company Overview of AB Trust - AB International Value Fund



Snapshot People




Company Overview
AB Trust - AB International Value Fund is an open ended equity mutual fund launched and managed by AllianceBernstein L.P. The fund invests in the public equity markets across the globe excluding the United States. It invests in the stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. The fund invests in the value stocks of companies operating across all market capitalizations. It employs a combination of fundamental and quantitative analysis by focusing on factors such as stocks priced low in relation to their perceived long-term earnings power, competitive position, economic cycle, forecasts for real economic growth, inflation, and interest rate changes to create its portfolio. The fun...
AB Trust - AB International Value Fund is an open ended equity mutual fund launched and managed by AllianceBernstein L.P. The fund invests in the public equity markets across the globe excluding the United States. It invests in the stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. The fund invests in the value stocks of companies operating across all market capitalizations. It employs a combination of fundamental and quantitative analysis by focusing on factors such as stocks priced low in relation to their perceived long-term earnings power, competitive position, economic cycle, forecasts for real economic growth, inflation, and interest rate changes to create its portfolio. The fund benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the MSCI EAFE Index (net). It employs internal research to create its portfolio. The fund was formerly known as AllianceBernstein Trust - AllianceBernstein International Value Fund. AB Trust - AB International Value Fund was formed on March 29, 2001 and is domiciled in the United States.
